C Programming Syllabus

This is a structured and comprehensive HTML document that outlines the core syllabus of the C Programming Language. It presents each chapter with detailed content and internal navigation, making it ideal for educational use, revision, or curriculum planning.

📌 Description

The C Programming Syllabus project offers a well-organized presentation of key concepts in the C language. Designed entirely with HTML, it breaks down complex topics into digestible chapters, from basic syntax to file handling. This project is helpful for students, teachers, and self-learners looking to understand the flow and scope of C programming.

🔧 Technologies Used

HTML5 (Only HTML – No CSS/JS frameworks used)


📄 Features

Clickable chapter links for easy navigation

Detailed content for each topic:

Introduction to C

Data types, operators, and expressions

Control flow mechanisms

Functions and recursion

Arrays and pointers

Structures, unions, and enums

File I/O operations


Semantic structure using headings and paragraphs

Simple inline styling for better readability


🚀 How to Use

1. Clone or download the repository.


2. Open the code.html file in any modern web browser.


3. Click on chapter titles to jump to specific topics.



📁 Project Structure

c-programming-syllabus/
├── code.html   # The main HTML file containing the full syllabus
└── README.md   # Project documentation

🔒 Note

This is a static educational resource. It does not contain interactive scripts or backend processing. You can expand it using CSS or JavaScript for additional functionality like collapsible sections, search, or printable views.
